			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: This study is designed to investigate the so-called "principle of real truth" as justification valid jurisdictional actions of varied content that occur within the Brazilian criminal proceedings. If questions the existence of this principle since there is no philosophical basis that validate as valid form within the legal framework. In addition, it questions the relationship that principle guard with a criminal justice system that does not respect the prerogatives of human dignity represented through the observance of human and fundamental rights.					<B>Objectives</B>: The research part of the analysis of what is usually called the real truth as a result of the inquisitorial system and whether it would be possible to extract a "real truth" compared to the legal and philosophical debates than is usually called truth.
So try to understand the motivation of the courts who decide to use it in their foundations.
He sought to contrast the achievements and changes resulting from the criminal garantismo front of inquisitive remnants of the Penal Procedure Code and the practical effects of this regulatory inconsistency.
He sought also to make clear that the search for a decent legal system of a so-called "rule of law" must necessarily go through the unconditional respect for human and fundamental rights of citizens by controlling the state punitive power.					<B>Methods</B>: The content of this research project it is an essentially theoretical and philosophical theme.
Although there is vast scientific literature specifically on the main theme, namely the principle of real truth in criminal proceedings, as originally thought, there is no denying that the issues related to this have been object of numerous studies. Thus, there was no difficulty in discuss topics such as inquisitive and accusatory criminal procedural systems, and philosophical discussions about what was meant by truth or compiled quality about the Theory of Criminal garantismo.
At the same time, interesting works popping eyes of researching such that the work of the renowned jurist Lênio Luiz Streck called "The Real Truth and Fiction of the symptoms of Philosophical Understanding Lack of Procedural Science", where there is criticism of the way, lacking of philosophical reflection, in which it is thought the legal science, particularly the criminal procedural law in Brazil.
Other works stood out for its content and were of vital importance for further research, such as "Law and Reason: Theory of Criminal garantismo", the precursor of criminal garantismo, Luigi Ferrajoli, "Critical Introduction to the Theory of Criminal garantismo" by Aury Lopes Junior, a great comparison between classical garantista theory and the unprecedented protection of human and fundamental rights brought by the 1988 Constitution.
Articles found online have been carefully selected in order to be used in the search only those with serious content. In this regard, it highlights essentially legal content sites such that: [e]lt;http://www.conjur.com.br/[e]rt;, or [e]lt;http://www.jurisway.org.br/[e]rt;.
